Executive Profile
Brian D. Finn  Investment Partner, Nyca PartnersAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 9 Board Members in 9 different organizations across 13 different industries.See Board Relationships57--
Background

		Mr. Brian D. Finn serves as an Investment Partner at Nyca Partners. Mr. Finn serves as a Strategic Advisor at KKR. He has over 30 years of experience in the financial services industry as well as a variety of corporate and philanthropic board roles. Mr. Finn served as the Chief Executive Officer at Asset Management Finance LLC from June 2009 to March 2013 and also served as its Chairman from August 2008 to March 2013. He served as the President at Credit Suisse (Deutschland) ... Aktiengesellschaft. He served as Senior Advisor of Credit Suisse (USA), Inc. and Credit Suisse Asset Management (Deutschland) GmbH. Mr. Finn held many positions at Credit Suisse and its predecessor firms, including President at Credit Suisse First Boston (now Credit Suisse AG) since July 2004 and Chief Executive Officer at Credit Suisse (USA), Inc. until April 19, 2005. He served as Chief Executive Officer of Credit Suisse USA and a member of the Office of the Chairman of CSFB. He was employed at Credit Suisse Private Equity, LLC. From 2004 to 2008, Mr. Finn served as the Chairman and Head of Alternative Investments at Credit Suisse Group AG. He served as a Partner at Clayton, Dubilier & Rice, Inc. from 1997 to 2002 and previously served as its Principal. He began his career in 1982 as a Member of the Mergers & Acquisitions Group at The First Boston Corporation, becoming co-head of M&A in 1993. He served as President of New York Investment Bank at Credit Suisse Group AG since July 2004. Mr. Finn served as Interim Head of investment banking at Credit Suisse Group AG since October 29, 2004, Member of the Executive Board since January 2003 and also served as its President of Investment Banking. He served as a Member of the Executive Board for Credit Suisse First Boston since 2003, Head of Alternative Capital since April 19, 2005 and Co-President of Institutional Securities from 2002 to July 2004. He served as the Head of Alternative Investments/Chairman of Alternative Investments Business and Chairman at Credit Suisse Asset Management, LLC from 2004 to 2009. Previously, he was an Operating Partner at Star Mountain Capital, LLC. He serves as Chairman of Advisory Board at Covr Financial Technologies, LLC. Mr. Finn serves as the Chairman of Star Mountain Capital, LLC. He serves as the Chairman of Tunbridge Partners LLC. He serves as Director of WaveGuide Corporation. He has been an Independent Director at BlackRock Kelso Capital Corporation since June 17, 2013. He has been a Director of Nu-Kote Holding, Inc. since November 1993 and Owl Rock Capital Corporation since May 4, 2016. He serves on the Board of China Renaissance Capital. He serves as a Director of Duff & Phelps Corporation, Telemundo, MGM Pictures, Nu-Kote International, U.S. Office Products, Dynatech, iship.com and ICO-Teledesic. Mr. Finn has been an Independent Director of The Scotts Miracle-Gro Company since December 1, 2014. He has been an Independent Director of BlackRock Capital Investment Corporation since June 17, 2013. He serves as a Director of Digital Lifeboat, Inc. He served as a Director of ICO Global Limited. Mr. Finn served as a Director of Harrisdirect LLC, Telecommunications Techniques Co., LLC and Baxter International Inc. He served as Unit Board Member at Credit Suisse Asset Management, LLC until 2009. He served as a Director at Clayton, Dubilier & Rice, Inc. He served as a Director of Asset Management Finance LLC since August 2008, Credit Suisse (USA), Inc. from December 2002 to April 19, 2005, Acterna Corp. since May 21, 1998 and Woods Cross Holding Corp. since June 1998. He served as the Chairman of the Undergraduate Executive Board of The Wharton School, Vice Chairman of the board of the City Kids Foundation, a Member of the Board of the Intrepid Fallen Heroes Fund, the Gordon A. Rich Memorial Foundation and the Starmar Foundation. He received B.S. in Economics from The Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.Read Full Background




